'''Level 28''' is the '''29<sup>th</sup>''' level of '''[[The Backrooms]]''' and seems to be connected to '''[[Level 27]]'''. '''Level 28''' is not to be confused with [[The Attic]].
==✦ Description==
<div style="text-align:left;">
{{Blurimage Border|width=350px|text-color=#e6d2b7|hovertext=The Attics|caption=<center>''The attic was dusty and misty; what is there to see?''{{Underline|e6d2b7}}{{Underline|e6d2b7}}A photograph of '''Level 28'''.|𝚏𝚒𝚐=1.0|file=Level19.jpg|border-color=#e6d2b7|box-shadow-color=null}}
'''Level 28''', also known as '''"The Attic"''' or '''"Crawlspace"''', appears to be a complex series of dusty, worn-down, old, inconsistent attic spaces, cluttered with boxes and beat-up furniture, with dim lighting that can be hard to find at times. The odd thing about this level is that there is absolutely no natural light; all of the light you can find is caused by an extremely faint glow with an unknown origin. It is recommended to bring your own lighting when entering this level, as it can be hard to navigate at times.

Light in the level is limited; the only way to see in this level is by utilizing an external light source. Otherwise, it is nearly impossible to traverse the level further. Additionally, '''Level 28''' possesses an anomalous effect that inhibits one's eyes' ability to adjust to the dark, leaving wanderers in pitch-black.

Small windows and vents occasionally appear in the ceiling, but all exterior light sources are absorbed by the darkness of the level, with only a dark blue tint visible through these windows. Vents do not appear to provide any form of circulation whatsoever. Vent pipes can be spotted along the sides of the level on occasion, connecting to the roof and the floor, and sometimes stretching along the walls. The main hazard at this level is the pink insulation on the floor, estimated at 1-3 feet thick.
{{Blurimage Border|width=350px|text-color=#e6d2b7|hovertext=The Darkness|caption=<center>''Darkness Enshrouds''{{Underline|e6d2b7}}{{Underline|e6d2b7}}Another photograph of '''Level 28'''.|𝚏𝚒𝚐=2.0|file=0993fjvqzr581.jpg|border-color=#e6d2b7|box-shadow-color=null}}
Most of the insulation is covered with a layer of dust and other debris, making the surface appear white. Whereas normal insulation consists of fiberglass, rock, slag wool, cellulose, and other natural fibers, samples of '''Level 28's''' insulation contain a combination of arsenic, polonium, beryllium, and other hazardous metals. Aside from these lethal substances, the insulation is also strewn with tens of thousands of microscopic needles that can pierce skin and most fabrics.

The needles are presumed to contain trace amounts of [[Object 12|Liquid Pain]], causing intense pain or worse if one were to come into contact with these needles. To prevent this, it is highly recommended to wear proper footwear, as most sneakers and dress shoes are resistant to these needles. When traversing the level, wanderers should always remain upright unless one is equipped with protective clothing approved by the [[M.E.G.]].

There have been debates over whether the insulation is a separate entity, but most have dismissed these claims, classifying it as a highly hazardous object. The effects of the insulation are exacerbated by the air, which is similarly highly toxic. Although it is not dangerous enough to quickly kill a human, inhaling the air without wearing professional equipment can cause a variety of health effects such as dizziness, shortness of breath, headaches, and, if one remains in the level for too long without proper equipment, asphyxiation. 

Official tests to determine the composition of the air in this level have not been approved, but [[M.E.G.]] experts have speculated that it contains high concentrations of nitrogen gas (N2) and carbon dioxide (CO2).
{{Blurimage Border|width=350px|text-color=#e6d2b7|hovertext=The Ladder|caption=<center>''Entrances Lurk''{{Underline|e6d2b7}}{{Underline|e6d2b7}}An entrance to '''Level 28''' from [[Level 27]].|𝚏𝚒𝚐=3.0|file=27 to 28 connection.png|border-color=#e6d2b7|box-shadow-color=null}}
'''Level 28''' is an attic of [[Level 27]], connecting it to that level by some ladders. Entering [[Level 27]] through the ladder, then looking back up at the ladder, will have a 50% chance to disappear. If it doesn't disappear, you will be sent to [[Level 14]]. If you enter through the ladder, you might faint and fall down the ladder. After you wake up, you will appear in '''Level 28'''.

In [[Level 27]], you could see wooden beams planted in the floors, which would mean that the wanderer is closer to the entrance to '''Level 28'''. The music you are hearing right now will slowly get louder as you get closer to the ladder. There are about 5 ladders in the whole of [[Level 27]].

The wood structure seems inadequate, perhaps due to age, and can be easily destroyed. As with the floor, when a person puts on too much weight, the wooden panels may collapse at specific locations and fall into the space beneath the bottom, which might cause injury. The use of this concealed, empty space and its connection to the attic room remain undetermined. The pit depth isn't sufficient to be lethal, yet there seems to be an additional empty crawlspace beneath the floor. Some attic rooms may already have shattered floors, resulting in massive openings deep down into the floor; it is unclear whether these deep holes were always present or caused by the traveler; nonetheless, no repairs will be made to these structures.
{{Blurimage Border|width=350px|text-color=#e6d2b7|hovertext=The Ripped Flooring|caption=<center>''I don't like this place; alone trying to find what is within..''{{Underline|e6d2b7}}{{Underline|e6d2b7}}An area with ripped flooring.|𝚏𝚒𝚐=4.0|file=19three.webp|border-color=#e6d2b7|box-shadow-color=null}}
Substantial disorganization of boxes, vintage furniture, and other miscellaneous stuff may rarely occur in the corners of rooms. '''Level 28's''' packaging consists of cardboard boxes sealed with tape and dusted. Inside are frequently critical meals, electrical appliances, and cataloged goods indispensable for life. Additionally, cobwebs may be seen on the walls, although none imply that spiders or other living beings are likely culprits.

[[Object 1|Almond Water]] may seep and drop from the ceiling, emerging from nowhere. Although this leaking water can continue perpetually, it can also produce large puddles. It raises the question of whether there were any significant sources of [[Object 1|Almond Water]] above the roof.

Several wanderers claim they hear a faint sound of rain when listening carefully, although it's most likely a false sound caused by the level's anomalous properties. Glowing boards can be found in some sections of '''Level 28''', which glisten. Touching the glowing boards can cause seizures or electric shocks; therefore, they should not be touched. Be careful when walking around on '''Level 28'''!
{{Blurimage Border|width=350px|text-color=#e6d2b7|hovertext=The Ripped Flooring|caption=<center>''Do we know anything about this place?''{{Underline|e6d2b7}}{{Underline|e6d2b7}}One of the insulation areas.|𝚏𝚒𝚐=5.0|file=19four.webp|border-color=#e6d2b7|box-shadow-color=null}}
The deeper areas of '''Level 28''' become more unstable and stranger the longer you explore. Hallways that once connected to cramped attic rooms may now extend into excessively long crawlspaces decorated with exposed beams and hanging wires, while certain routes shrink to the point that movement becomes nearly impossible.

In certain areas, the ceiling seems unusually high, disappearing into darkness where no light sources can work properly. Wanderers have reported hearing movement above the roof, despite there being no visible entities, as well as banging sounds that repeat in odd patterns throughout '''Level 28'''. Although '''Level 28''' appears abandoned at first, signs of previous colonies become more common as the wanderer wanders deeper inside, such as stained mattresses, extinguished lamps, handwritten notes, and barricades made of broken furniture.

Most of these shelters appear to have been abandoned for years, while some contain recent lightbulbs, implying that someone <small>(or something)</small> was around not long ago. As wanderers "wander" through '''Level 28''', the environment starts to distort. Certain crawlspaces loop back into themselves. Chambers that do not fit within the attic's structure. As wanderers "wander" through '''Level 28''', the environment starts to distort. Certain crawlspaces loop back into themselves. Chambers that do not fit within the attic's structure. Some wanderers report finding entire chambers filled with stacked furniture towers that extend from floor to ceiling, making labyrinth-like passages between unstable piles of cabinets, mirrors, and ancient wardrobes.

==✦ Anomalies/Phenomena==
{{Blurimage Border|width=350px|text-color=#e6d2b7|hovertext=The Virus|caption=<center>''How do we get out of here..?''{{Underline|e6d2b7}}{{Underline|e6d2b7}}The only picture of The Virus found from a microscope.|𝚏𝚒𝚐=6.0|file=28Virus.png|border-color=#e6d2b7|box-shadow-color=null}}
'''Level 28''' possesses a plethora of anomalous effects which have undermined efforts to further document this level. Among them is an anomalous effect unique to '''Level 28''', informally dubbed "The Virus". This anomaly manifests in an array of symptoms, some of which have previously been delineated, such as the level's ability to inhibit the human eye's process of adjusting to the dark. Symptoms of the '''Level 28''' effect occur when wanderers first enter this level.

One will immediately fall into a state of panic and anxiety, causing The Wretched Cycle to take effect quickly. The only ways to stop and/or slow this effect are drinking [[Object 1|Almond Water]] or activating a light source and proceeding to shine the light on every surface within a few-meter radius of them. If any surface is left unchecked, the effects will stop, but an overhanging sense of dread will remain until the wanderer shines a light source on the unchecked surfaces.
==✦ Entities==
The level is presumed to not just be a run-down attic, but a complex of planks, some are also crawlspaces, passages, and sometimes stairs that lead down to lower areas, which are much more open compared to where the wanderer will end up upon arrival in this level Taking these stairs is not all too recommended though, due to the Death Moths that reside down below the main areas.

There have been some confirmed reports of [[Entity 3|Smilers]], [[Entity 72|Foams]], and [[Phenomenon 35|Wretches]] roaming the level. Corpses of [[Entity 10|Skin-Stealers]] and [[Entity 8|Hounds]] have allegedly been discovered on the sides of '''Level 28''', although none of these claims have been successfully substantiated.
{{Entity Class|Agg=5|Dan=5|Int=4|no=N/A|Hab=[[Level 28]] and [[Level 799]].}}
{{Blurimage Border|width=350px|text-color=#e6d2b7|hovertext=You're screwed.|caption=<center>''What may this be?''{{Underline|e6d2b7}}{{Underline|e6d2b7}}The lanky creature in an unknown level. Photographer dead.|𝚏𝚒𝚐=7.0|file=SoDead28.webp|border-color=#e6d2b7|box-shadow-color=null}}
'''Attic Dwellers''' are long, tall black stickman figures with white eyes and lurk around the ark. These entities have high IQ, which will make them find you very quickly. They can be distinguished very easily because of how non-human they are. '''Attic Dwellers''' are usually longer and skinnier than humans but are never above 4 feet. Because of their height, it can be hard for them to get through structures, which can help you escape from them. People can appear to be any sex, but all '''Attic Dwellers''' are sexless and cannot reproduce. Thus, it is endangered as it is disappearing very quickly. They can die by shooting guns at it.

It appears to be a black, voided stick figure about 3 feet tall; it stalks you and tries to kill you. Its body appears to be a weird, humanoid-feeling texture. '''Attic Dwellers''' have skin that is not only wrinkled but also sticky and oily. Its brain is small, likely due to evolutionary constraints, and it is unable to speak or produce sounds. Its feet have been adapted for running and crawling in tight spaces; its body has almost no organs, containing only a heart, brain, and eyes. It stands still before sucking you in it's body.
<div style="text-align:left;">
==✦ Colonies & Outposts/Communities==
Due to '''Level 28's''' instabilities and hazards, no colonies or communities can be made. Some possible colonies and outposts/communities seem to have existed before but are now gone.
==✦ Entrances & Exits==
===Entrances===
{{Blurimage Border|width=350px|text-color=#e6d2b7|hovertext=The Abyss|caption=<center>''The Abyss''{{Underline|e6d2b7}}{{Underline|e6d2b7}}An image of wooden beams stretched into the abyss.|𝚏𝚒𝚐=8.0|file=Level19-1.jpg|border-color=#e6d2b7|box-shadow-color=null}}
*One may come across "Holes" in the relatively small walls on [[Level 1]]. If one crawls through these openings, they can get to '''Level 28''', and the entrance will disappear behind them—it is also rumored that these entrances can appear on [[Level 4]] and [[Level 8]]. However, this data doesn't have enough evidence to be confirmed.
*A trapdoor can occasionally appear on [[Level 27]]'s ceiling; climbing up will get one here.
*A wooden box with a clock in [[Level 80]] MAY send one here.
===Exits===
*Boxes may contain old and decayed consoles. Activating one will noclip one to [[Level 25]], although using the same consoles in other levels won't do anything.
*Noclipping through a pile of discarded tickets sends one to [[Level 154]].
*Areas that exhibit higher ceilings also sometimes feature slightly damaged wooden doors. These doors are reported to take one to [[Level 483]], [[Level 5]], [[Level 12]], [[Level 19]], [[Level 20]], and [[Level 42]] all with a random chance.
*Windows may appear at the dead ends, breaking through them will noclip one to [[Level 9]], [[Level 38]], [[Level 597]], or [[Level 39]].
*Successfully breaking open the roof will forcefully no-clip the wanderer into [[Level 398]].
*Certain areas of this level will lead to [[Level 0.7]].
*Going to larger areas will lead to [[Level 27.3]].
*Climbing down a ladder will send you to [[Level 27]].
*Finding a desolate wooden box with a door in '''Level 28''' will be another exit. If the room looks party-like, it will send you to [[Level 90]]. If the room has nothing in it, you will be sent to [[Level 10]].
Note that [[Level 0]] and '''Level 28''' are the only confirmed levels that feature an egress to [[Level 483]].

